HEADWORD: Frondent
<hw>Fron"dent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frondens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>frondere</ets> to put forth leaves.
See <er>Frond</er>.]</ety> <def>Covered with leaves; leafy; <as>as, a
<ex>frondent</ex> tree</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frondesce</ent>⟦br⟧
